# Lightning Strikes

Short, explosive sprint intervals that build raw neuromuscular power. Each 30-second effort should be absolutely maximal — empty the tank every time. The long recoveries mean you should be fully ready for each sprint.

- 10:00 50%
  - :30 Warm up — we'll build into the sprints
  - 5:00 Get the blood flowing, open up the lungs
  - 3:00 Sprints start in 2 minutes — find a gear you can accelerate hard in
  - :30 Get ready — first one in 30 seconds
- 8x
  - :30 150%
    - :05 FULL GAS — out of the saddle!
    - :20 Hold it hold it hold it!
  - 2:30 40%
    - :10 Breathe — that's one down
    - 1:30 Next sprint in 1 minute, get your breath back
    - :20 Coming up — hands in the drops
- 5:00 50%
  - :10 Halfway through — 4 more to go
  - 3:00 Easy spinning, let the heart rate settle
  - 1:00 Round two starts in 1 minute
- 4x
  - :30 160%
    - :05 DIG DIG DIG — harder than the first set!
    - :20 Don't sit down!
  - 2:30 40%
    - :10 Recover fully
    - 1:30 Next sprint in 1 minute
- 5:00 40%
  - :10 That's all 12 sprints — incredible power!
  - 3:00 Spin it out, let everything come back down
